
HowTo install libg3d (tested on Debian)

* install all neccessary libs (gtk und glib)
* execute this little shell scripts to link glib header files into the include directory
  -> LIBS=`ls /usr/include/glib-2.0/`; for lib in $LIBS; do echo $lib; ln -s /usr/include/glib-2.0/$lib /usr/include/$lib; done
  -> LIBS=`ls /usr/lib/glib-2.0/include/`; for lib in $LIBS; do echo $lib; ln -s /usr/lib/glib-2.0/include/$lib /usr/include/$lib; done
* compile and install libg3d
* add '/usr/local/lib' to your /etc/ld.so.conf file and run `ldconfig` to apply changes



HowTo compile 3dsloader_g3d

* install libg3d  ;-)
* copy example-Makefile.am to s3d/example/Makefile.am after making a backup of the original Makefile.am
* run `export LDFLAGS="-lm -lg3d"` before using configure
